[The most recent data on mass drug administration (MDA) to control and ultimately eradicate lymphatic filariasis in India show a coverage of 88 percent (http://nvbdcp.gov.in/mda.html). Co-administration of DEC with Albendazole during MDA is standard and the overall microphilaria rate decreased from 1.2 percent in 2004 to 0.3 percent in 2013 (Prov.) (http://nvbdcp.gov.in/mda.html).

The term "flull blown disease" used here is not well defined and the difference between the 126 cases with "full blown disease" and 132 with "chronic filarial swelling" is unclear. The key numbers are that 2245 were new diagnosed cases of lymphatic filariasis and that 132 cases had chronic filariasis with lymphedema. Maharashtra state has 114 million inhabitants (2012), which is 1 case per roughly 50 000 inhabitants, still below the overall figure of 0.3 percent positivity cited by the ministry of health (http://nvbdcp.gov.in/mda.html). - Mod.EP

